      "line": "You already know periods (.), commas (,), exclamation (!), and question marks (?). In Spanish writing you’ll also see opening signs at the start of a question or exclamation — an upside-down question mark (¿) and an upside-down exclamation mark (¡). They warn your voice early that a question or shout is coming."
    },
    {
      "phase": "meaning_depth",
      "origin": "In the 1700s, printers formalized opening marks so readers could set the right tone from the very first word.",
